description: The earthquake that occurred near Katmandu, Nepal, touched off avalanches on Mount Everest causing injury and death during prime climbing season.
title: Earthquake Causes Avalanche on Everest
title_page: Earthquake Causes Avalanche on Everest - The New York Times
maintext:
The avalanche trapped climbers on the upper slopes.
Approximate location of the avalanche that killed 16 a year ago.
Members of an expedition report no injuries from Saturday’s avalanche.
“Our camp was in a good place, we got dusted but here at Camp 1 we were just fine.”
